Detailed Description

Vector containing pointers to SubRoutes.

This is used as request and reply in RouteModule, and as result vector containing the SubRoutes making up the finished route. Note that there is no way of dequeueing from this class. To access members that you do not want to remain in the vector, use 'getSubRouteAt' and then 'resetIndex'.

The SubRoutes still in the SubRouteVector when the SubRouteVector is deleted are deleted.
